<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>CAB: 7000 AND 8000 SERIES MODELS - REMOVAL AND INSTALLATION - Windshield Washer Pump Motor</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Windshield Washer Pump Motor</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Removal</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <randlist type="bullet">
                        <item>
                            <para>The pump motor is removable from the washer bottle without removing the washer bottle.
                                The pump motor is serviceable and replaced as a unit.
                            </para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Pump motor location is under driver side door for all models except 8600 which is
                                under the passenger side door.
                            </para>
                        </item>
                    </randlist>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f1603849" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg16/G1603849.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 67. Windshield Washer Pump Motor</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. ELECTRICAL CONNECTOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. WASHER BOTTLE</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. PUMP MOTOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. WINDSHIELD WASHER HOSE</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para></para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect electrical connector from pump motor.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place a container under the washer bottle to catch the windshield washer fluid.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect windshield washer hose from pump motor.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove pump motor by carefully pulling it straight out of the washer bottle.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Installation</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The pump motor can be installed on the washer bottle without removing the washer bottle. The
                        pump motor is serviceable and replaced as a unit.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the pump motor by carefully pushing the pump motor straight into the washer
                    bottle (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1603849">Figure 67, Items 2 and 3</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect windshield washer hose to pump motor (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1603849">Figure 67, Items 3 and 4</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect electrical connector to pump motor (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1603849">Figure 67, Items 1 and 3</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Fill washer bottle with windshield washer solvent and check for leaks and washer
                    operation.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
